 Requirements:
 -------------
 The install requires WHDLoad and RAWDIC to be in the path. Both can be found
 in the WHDLoad package.
 To install from a different drive than DF0: select installation mode Expert.
 
 The installed program requires 0.5 MB ChipMem (+1.3Mb other memory for preload 
 option).
 
 It can be quit by pressing * (key can be changed with Tooltype "QuitKey=").
 
 The installed program requires WHDLoad 17+
 
 NOTE: This version is not compatible with previously saved high scores.  The
 previous high score file is missing data.
 
 Features:
 ---------
 - System friendly imager
 - Press '*' to quit (Configurable)
 - Load/Save scores to HD
 - Added new icons by IrekÂ´72
 - Added BUTTONWAIT tooltype support (for those people who want
   to see the screen with the helmet)
 - Custom1=1 - Activate programmers cheat
 - Custom2=1 - Invincibility

 Joypad support (joypad automatically detected)
	Red 				- Fire
	Play 				- Pause 
	Play+Forward+Reverse 		- Quit (Port 2 only)
	Yellow+Green+Forward+Reverse 	- Abort Game (Port 2 only)

   Title Screen
	Play 				- Enter Options Screen 

   Options Screen
	Reverse (Port 2)		- F1 (select Joy 1)
	Forward (Port 2)		- F2 (select Joy 2)
	Reverse (Port 1)		- F6 (select Joy 1)
	Forward (Port 1)		- F7 (select Joy 2)

 History:
 --------
 Version 1.5 (20/05/2018) by JOTD:
 - Custom3=1 now enables 2-button mode for jeep (arcade-like controls):
   moving cannon doesn't need fire, blue/2nd button jumps
 - Automatic joypad detection for both players
 - Fixed menu crash when joypad controls are enabled
 
 Version 1.4 (26/02/2018) by JOTD:
 - jeep player controls defaults to joystick in port 1 instead of keyboard (unless CUSTOM4 is set)
 - adapted to WHDLoad v17 (dynamic options on splash screen, rewritten patchlists with conditionals)
 - fixed "bug" which prevented to crunch files with Propack or such (resload_LoadFile => resload_LoadFileDecrunch)
 - if invincibility cheat mode is enabled, high scores aren't saved anymore
 
 Version 1.3 (10/17/2011) by Keith Krellwitz (Abaddon)
 - Complete re-write using Patchlists
 - Fixed issue with saving/loading highscores
 - Fixed bug in top score for jeep and heli displayed on game screen. 
 - Added support for a 3rd version, thanks to IrekÂ´72 for the disk image.
 - New islave imager
 - Removed dependency on the incbin for the loader
 - Dropped JST specific code (Sorry JOTD / not a problem Abaddon!)
 - Added new icons by IrekÂ´72
 - Custom1=1 - Activate programmers cheat
 - Custom2=1 - Invincibility
 - Custom3=1 - Enable CD32 joypad support
	Red 				- Fire
	Play 				- Pause 
	Play+Forward+Reverse 		- Quit (Port 2 only)
	Yellow+Forward+Reverse 		- Abort Game (Port 2 only)

   Title Screen
	Play 				- Enter Options Screen 

   Options Screen
	Reverse (Port 2)		- F1 (select Joy 1)
	Forward (Port 2)		- F2 (select Joy 2)
	Reverse (Port 1)		- F6 (select Joy 1)
	Forward (Port 1)		- F7 (select Joy 2)

 Version 1.2 (12.05.03) by JOTD
 - empty dbf loops fixed
 - keyboard fixed
 - hiscores fixed

 Version 1.1 (2001) by JOTD
 - WHDLoad conversion
 - Access fault removed, which caused the game to crash in the middle

 JST Versions (1998-2000) by Abaddon/JOTD
 - Two versions supported (Thanks to Stepan Chladek for the 2nd version)
 - Saving of the high scores to HD on game exit (JST) or at once (WHDLoad)
 - User can RNC crunch files
 - System friendly imager
 - Added BUTTONWAIT tooltype support (for those people who want
   to see the screen with the helmet)
 - Possible to quit by pressing F10 (JST) or QUITKEY (WHDLoad)
 - Jeff: Iconify/Snapshot added (JST only)
   of level 1 (at least for one version).
 - Jeff: ripped/reworked a nice OS3.5 icon
   (I took the title at full scale, no resize, I personally think it's great :))

 CHEAT:
 ------

	Press F10 to access the Options Screen.  Now type "SCRAP 28", after 
	pressing 8, the lower half of the screen will flash. This will provide
	you with infinite lives and enable the following keys:
	- Press the mumber keys and '-' to select levels. 
	- Use the function keys for variable slow motion.
	
	This cheat works with IPF 0388

	On early versions, before pressing fire to start the game, hold down
	"HELP" and then press fire.  Now use the keys mentioned above during
	play. This cheat works with IPF 2413 and non IPF V3

 Contact:
 --------
 If you have problems with this installation please try and get a newer
 version of this package from the WHDLoad WWW-Page. If that doesn't help try
 some Tooltypes like NOCACHE, NOAUTOVEC, EXPCHIP, NOMMU, PAL or NTSC. If
 that also fails, please inform the author via the Bug-Report-Form which
 can be accessed on the WHDLoad WWW-Page or create a mantis issue directly
 at http://mantis.whdload.de

 For the full WHDLoad package, other installs and updates refer to:
	http://www.whdload.de/
 or	aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
 and	aminet:game/patch/

